<subSubSection id="CF692784B07F8906F29413F8EAB0B149" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="957A958FE2D2A23433EF6B0824798D49" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E65685AA2EFCA954041A50EE105F866" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
No DNA sequences from 
<taxonomicName id="D44FB1DA9CAEABA915322E966CCA6AA4" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Xenidae</taxonomicName>
parasitizing 
<taxonomicName id="7DDD856279BE7E44D92DB8E2F586E381" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Stenodynerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenodynerus" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C936703DB30983E0E59CF63CC8845FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Stenodynerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Saussure in East Asia have been available. Strepsipterans parasitizing 
<taxonomicName id="C15CF44EEF8D268BE343D932D69737AE" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Stenodynerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenodynerus" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F22229070FE206E3089AB6109FB8F9CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Stenodynerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Japan are preliminarily included in 
<taxonomicName id="EA306C32F7D1DF484951642947C698EA" authority="Benda, Pohl, Nakase, Beutel &amp; Straka, 2022" authorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Deltoxenos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltoxenos" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B29038E18347571D6C91E11F4ED6DCFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Deltoxenos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. here based on their morphology, which, however, should be supported by future molecular phylogenetic analyses.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
